Prosecutors said Frank was the victim of the fastest-growing crime in America: identity theft.
The Identity Theft and Assumption Deterrence Act of 1998 makes it a felony to commit identity theft.
``Back in 1988 when it happened (to me), nobody even knew what I was talking about,'' said Elsie Strong of Los Angeles, founder of the support group Victims of Identity Theft
